VALUES ('Catfish-Channel.png', 'Catfish, Channel', 'River Catfish, Spotted Cat, Blue Channel Catfish', 'No', 'The channel catfish is usually bluish olive, gray or black on the upper part of the body, becoming white below. Dark spots are usually scattered along the sides. Older males are dark in color, the head looking very wide when seen from the top. Channel catfish have long barbels surrounding the mouth and the tail is deeply forked.

This species is often confused with the Blue Catfish which is another species.

